# FlipSentry UI Port

## Scope

- Work in **heroui-mobile** only for implementation.
- **mobile-app** is screen/flow reference only - do not copy NativeWind, shadcn, MobX, or API clients.

## Data

- UI + mock only. All reads/writes go through `src/mocks/services/*` and fixtures in `src/mocks/data/*`.
- Never use Axios, SignalR, Adapty, or real backends in this repo.

## Theme

- Uber-inspired neutrals via HeroUI tokens in `src/global.css` (oklch grayscale).
- Dark: near-black background, white `--accent` / black `--accent-foreground`.
- Light: light gray background, black `--accent` / white `--accent-foreground`.
- Prefer semantic classes (`bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `bg-accent`) - no legacy green/black hardcodes (`#1DB954`, `#121212`).
- Use `Button variant="secondary"` for most actions; primary/accent sparingly (Uber black/white).

## Components

- Prefer `heroui-native-pro`, then `heroui-native` (OSS), then minimal custom (e.g. map placeholder).
- Do not use web `@heroui/react` / `@heroui-pro/react` for screens.
- Style with Uniwind `className` - not NativeWind / StyleSheet for colors.

## Agent workflow

- Before building a screen, use Native Pro MCP: `list_components` → `get_component_docs`.
- Follow `PORTING.md` folder layout and port order (shell → auth → feed → home → settings → subscription).
